      "Clauses related to notices, audits, and integration (GC-NO, GC-AR, GC-EA) include Notice Provisions, Audit Rights, and Entire Agreement.",
      "The notice provisions clause (GC-NO) determines when any required notices are considered legally effective. Templates sometimes include notice mechanisms that make communications effective on dispatch rather than receipt; the Pro-Library Version requires written notice through defined channels with actual receipt requirements. The Reasonable Fallback gives flexibility on timing while keeping the structure mutual.",
      "The audit rights clause (GC-AR) covers what the vendor can audit and how. The Pro-Library Version limits audits to use of the licensed content, requires reasonable notice, caps frequency at once per year, puts costs on the vendor, excludes patron information protected by state library confidentiality laws, and restricts audits to parties in direct privity with the vendor (which prevents the vendor from reaching consortium members or affiliated libraries that have no direct contractual relationship with the vendor).",
      "Finally, the entire agreement clause (GC-EA) determines what external documents are considered part of the contract. The Pro-Library Version restricts what gets incorporated by limiting incorporations to only those documents expressly attached as exhibits."
